<section class="section">
  <div class="section-inner">
    <div class="sec-eyebrow">About pancreatic cancer</div>
    <h2 class="sec-h"><span class="te-content">Pancreatic Cancer — <em>Honest Assessment</em></span><span class="en-content">Pancreatic Cancer — <em>Honest Assessment</em></span></h2>
    <div class="prose">
      <div class="te-block">
        <p>నేను pancreatic cancer patients కి ఒక honest thing చెప్తాను. Surgery possible అయిన cases లో (resectable cases) surgery ఒక్కటే currently long-term survival offer చేయగలదు. కానీ, diagnosis అయిన cases లో దాదాపు 15-20% మాత్రమే upfront resectable. మిగతా cases లో neoadjuvant chemotherapy తరువాత reassessment అవసరం.</p>
        <p>Whipple's Procedure (pancreaticoduodenectomy) pancreatic head cancers కి standard. AIIMS లో నా training లో ఈ procedure high volume లో చేశాను. ISGPS (International Study Group on Pancreatic Surgery) guidelines follow చేస్తాను.</p>
        <p>Surgeon volume matters enormously here. Published literature: low-volume centres లో Whipple's mortality 10-15%, high-volume specialised centres లో 2-3%. ఇది choice of surgeon కి important consideration.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="en-block">
        <p>I tell pancreatic cancer patients one honest thing. In cases where surgery is possible (resectable cases), surgery is currently the only treatment that can offer long-term survival. But only about 15-20% of diagnosed cases are upfront resectable. The rest need reassessment after neoadjuvant chemotherapy.</p>
        <p>Whipple's Procedure (pancreaticoduodenectomy) is the standard for pancreatic head cancers. During my AIIMS training, I performed this procedure in high volumes. I follow ISGPS (International Study Group on Pancreatic Surgery) guidelines.</p>
        <p>Surgeon volume matters enormously here. Published literature shows mortality at low-volume centres is 10-15% for Whipple's, compared to 2-3% at high-volume specialised centres. That is an important consideration in choosing a surgeon.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
<section class="section section-grey">
  <div class="section-inner">
    <div class="sec-eyebrow">Surgical options</div>
    <h2 class="sec-h"><span class="te-content">Surgery <em>Options</em></span><span class="en-content">Surgical <em>Options</em></span></h2>
    <div class="proc-list">
      <div class="proc-item"><div class="proc-tier">T2</div><div class="proc-body"><h4>Whipple's Procedure (Pancreaticoduodenectomy)</h4><p>For pancreatic head and periampullary cancers. Removes pancreatic head, duodenum, gallbladder and part of bile duct. 6-8 hour surgery, 7-10 day stay.</p><div class="proc-meta">AIIMS High-Volume Training · ISGPS Guidelines</div></div></div>
      <div class="proc-item"><div class="proc-tier">T2</div><div class="proc-body"><h4>Distal Pancreatectomy</h4><p>For cancers in body or tail of pancreas. Often combined with splenectomy. Laparoscopic approach in suitable cases.</p></div></div>
      <div class="proc-item"><div class="proc-tier">T2</div><div class="proc-body"><h4>Total Pancreatectomy</h4><p>For cancers involving the entire pancreas. Results in insulin-dependent diabetes. Only when necessary.</p></div></div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>


